      • getReferences

        public Iterable<String> getReferences()
        Description copied from interface: IItemReferenceIterable
        Get the references that are used to iterate through the items. Implementations are free to skip references and/or produce 1 or more items for each reference. The Strings returned must be dereferencable through the IItemReferenceIterable.dereference(List) and IItemReferenceIterable.dereference(String) methods.
        Specified by:
        getReferences in interface IItemReferenceIterable<T>
        Returns:
        an iterable that produces references in an order used to produce the items that are available from the iterator.

      • dereference

        public List<T> dereference(List<String> references)
        Description copied from interface: IItemReferenceIterable
        Get the item(s) at the underlying reference. Implementations may choose to loop on IItemReferenceIterable.dereference(String) or in some cases it may be more efficient to dereference in bulk.
        Specified by:
        dereference in interface IItemReferenceIterable<T>
        Returns:
